## Exfiltrating emails from a major refrigerator company

during a penetration test engagement 
relating to the external perimeter of one of the largest refrigeration companies,
we noticed a domain relating to a site from Romania where an outdated version of a Postfix was exposed,
from there we exfiltrated usernames and passwords using a SQLi , exchanges of recent emails and relating 
to more than 10 years ago containing information and criticisms, and all the other DBs, at this point however 
it was not enough for us and we wanted to definitively compromise the target, first we had to cpair where to 
write and where the reverse shell ended that we always wanted to load using SQLi, but the permissions did not 
allow us to do so until we tried to load using an exfiltrated user of an admin guy, from there we were able to 
load a shell and act with root privileges on the target machine. The customer was happy above all because he 
disliked his Romanian colleagues and was only waiting for their misstep to attack them, we were glad to have helped him.
